            "author_info": {
                "name": "Chris Mills",
                "href": "/profile/Chris-Mills-7"
            },
            "answer_text": "I write short fiction, but I am writing a novel now as well. With my short fiction, I often set the first draft aside and rewrite from scratch. The original draft is short and is still in my head. This works fine for short fiction. For my novel, I would not even consider setting the first draft aside and starting over. The process already takes a great deal of time and this would only add to that. But when it comes time for me to rewrite, I will not consider anything in my first draft to be sacred. That goes for individual words as well as plot and character development. ",
