                "name": "Darren Johnson",
                "href": "/profile/Darren-Johnson-27"
            },
            "answer_text": "Who knows? Some people write a pretty good novel in draft 1, and it just needs a solid copy edit. Some people write a sloppy mess but there are moments of goodness in it. Such novels may need massive revision \u2014 moving whole chapters, changing perspectives, adding scenes. If your novel is a complete mess but there are some nuggets of great writing within, I say start over from scratch, this time trying to write more tightly. ",
