            "answer_text": "Edit, edit, edit. Some authors go through 6 - 10 or more drafts before then consider a manuscript ready for other eyes. And find a writing group that will give you really good, actionable feedback. Listen to what they have to say. If it resonates, go back and rework your story until you know in your gut it is the best story you can make it. If you start with the why of your story, it will be much easier to keep you story on track. Here\u2019s a blog that explains starting with the why and an inciting incident. Hope it helps! What is the WHY of Your Story \u2013 Your First Fifteen Pages \u2013 Medium ",
