                "name": "Adrian G Hilder",
                "href": "/profile/Adrian-G-Hilder"
            },
            "answer_text": "That depends on whether your novel is well structured or not and you as a writer. Story Engineering by Larry Brooks will tell you if you have used an appropriate structure or not. If you have, you can probably edit from where you are. If you haven\u2019t a re-write with that structure in mind is probably best. You can ignore these structure \u2018rules\u2019 and take your chances that your story has enough narrative thrust without using these structure techniques. ",
