        {
            "author_info": {
                "name": "Henry Martin",
                "href": "/profile/Henry-Martin-16"
            },
            "answer_text": "It all depends on how good the draft is. You might have a great style, but a shitty plot. You might have a great plot, but shitty writing. You might have a bad plot and bad writing. Or, you might have gotten everything right. I\u2019d suggest putting the manuscript aside for a few weeks. Read something that you like, read something that you don\u2019t like. Just read to clear your mind. Then, once a few weeks pass, get your manuscript out and read it. You should see right away if there is something wrong with it, what it is, and how good/bad it reads. Address it from there. ",
